claim: Less than 14,550 people have died of COVID-19 as of March 22 , 2020 .
truth: As of 22 March , more than 334,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 14,500 deaths and 97,000 recoveries .

claim: Michigan 's stay at home extension order was protested by more than 1,000 motorists on April 15 , 2020 .
truth: On April 15 , a convoy of motorists drove from all over the state to protest the extension of Governor Gretchen Whitmer 's stay-at-home order .

claim: A person convicted of rape in Tasmania could be sentenced to serve up to 21 years in prison .
truth: Criminal Code Act 1899 ( QLD ) In Tasmania , rape is punishable under s 185 of the Criminal Code Act 1924 with a maximum punishment of 21 years under s389 of the Criminal Code Act 1924.Criminal Code 1924 ( TAS ) Sexual assault is considered a gendered crime which results in 85 % of sexual assaults never coming to the attention of the criminal justice system according to the Australian Bureau of Statistics .

claim: The F-19 is a hypothetical advanced fighter aircraft .
truth: F-19 is the designation for a hypothetical US fighter aircraft that has never been officially acknowledged , and has engendered much speculation that it might refer to a type of aircraft whose existence is still classified.

claim: Charlie Puth 's Attention has received positive reception from critics and listeners .

claim: Dave Mathews Band failed to sell more than 30 million records globally .
truth: As of 2010 , the Dave Matthews Band did not sold over 30 million records worldwide .

claim: License to Kill was the first film in the Bond franchise to get a PG-13 rating by the Motion Picture Association of America .
truth: The film earned over $ 156 million worldwide , and enjoyed a generally positive critical reception , with ample praise for the stunts , but attracted some criticism of Dalton 's dark and violent interpretation of Bond and the fact that the film was significantly darker and more violent than its predecessors , resulting in the film 's PG-13 rating by the Motion Picture Association of America ( the first for the franchise ) .

claim: There are more than 359,000 cases of COVID-19 as of 23 March .
truth: As of 23 March , more than 360,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 15,400 deaths and over 100,000 recoveries .

claim: Badmotorfinger was certified double platinum by the RIAA after March 1996 , as more than 1.8 million copies were sold ; however , less than 1.6 million copies had been sold before November 2010 .
truth: 136 Badmotorfinger was certified double platinum by the RIAA in April 1996 , signifying two million shipped copies ; however , only 1.5 million copies had been sold by October 2010.In a contemporary review for Spin , Lauren Spencer hailed Badmotorfinger as a `` garden of sound '' that drew on older hard rock influences without sounding `` derivative '' .

claim: In Taiwan , more than 50,000 people have been tested for coronavirus as of April 17 , 2020 .
truth: As of 17 April , 51,603 tests had been conducted in Taiwan with the vast majority not confirming a coronavirus diagnosis .
